# OSM Extractor - Harita Hive Data Tool
# MIT License
#
# Download OSM layers by bounding box or city name
# Automated extraction with format conversion and filtering
#
# Features:
# - Bounding box or place name extraction
# - Layer-specific filtering (roads, buildings, POIs)
# - Multiple output formats
# - Attribute filtering and selection
# - Automatic topology validation
# - Batch processing for multiple areas
#
# Data Sources:
# - Overpass API for current data
# - Planet OSM extracts
# - Regional OSM mirrors
# - Custom OSM databases
#
# Extraction Methods:
# - Bounding box coordinates
# - Administrative boundaries
# - City/region names
# - Custom polygon areas
# - Buffer around points/lines
#
# Output Formats:
# - Shapefile (.shp)
# - GeoJSON (.geojson)
# - GeoPackage (.gpkg)
# - PostGIS database
# - KML (.kml)
# - CSV with coordinates
#
# Layer Types:
# - Roads and transportation
# - Buildings and land use
# - Points of interest (POIs)
# - Administrative boundaries
# - Natural features
# - Custom tag filtering
#
# Usage:
# osm-extractor --city "San Francisco, CA" --layers roads,buildings --format shp
# osm-extractor --bbox -122.5,37.7,-122.3,37.8 --filter amenity=restaurant